South Africa Suspends Exports of Ostrich Meat, Live Birds After Flu Found

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-04-14T07:20:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/south-africa-suspends-exports-of-ostrich-meat-live-birds-after-flu-found.html
South Africa  has suspended exports
of all ostrich meat and live birds after an outbreak of avian
flu, Anton Kruger, a spokesman for the South African Ostrich
Business Chamber, said in an interview today.  The outbreak is isolated to one farm in Oudtshoorn, Wouter
Kriel, a spokesman for the Department of Agriculture, said
separately.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen in  Cape Town  at 
 lvanderwesth@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  